President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Mark Andrew Green as Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development. Green is currently serving as President of the International Republican Institute and has previous experience as the U.S. Ambassador to Tanzania. Trump also plans to nominate David J. Kautter as an Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for Tax Policy. Kautter is currently a Partner-in-Charge at RSM and has over 30 years of experience in tax consulting. Additionally, Trump announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts, including the President's Commission on White House Fellowships, the Commission on Combating Drug Addiction and the Opioid Crisis, and the United States Holocaust Memorial Council.